{"title_page": "Scappoose Industrial Airpark", "text_new": "{{Infobox Airport\n| name         = Scappoose Industrial Airpark\n| image        = Scappoose Industrial Airpark Oregon.jpg\n| caption      = Hangars, planes, and runway\n| IATA         = <!--not SPB-->\n| ICAO         = KSPB\n| FAA          = SPB\n| type         = Public\n| owner-oper   = Port of Columbia County\n| city-served  = [[Scappoose, Oregon]]\n| location     = <!--if different than above-->\n| elevation-f  = 58\n| elevation-m  = 18\n| coordinates  = {{coord|45|46|16|N|122|51|43|W|region:US-OR_type:airport_scale:10000}}\n| website      = [https://www.portofcolumbiacounty.org/business-and-development/page/scappoose-industrial-airpark/ Port of Columbia County]\n| r1-number    = 15/33\n| r1-length-f  = 5,100\n| r1-length-m  = 1,554\n| r1-surface   = [[Asphalt]]\n| stat-year    = 2009\n| stat1-header = Aircraft operations\n| stat1-data   = 75,500\n| stat2-header = Based aircraft\n| stat2-data   = 57\n| footnotes    = Source: [[Federal Aviation Administration]]<ref name=\"FAA\">{{FAA-airport|ID=SPB|use=PU|own=PU|site=19598.*A}}. Federal Aviation Administration. Effective 8 April 2010.</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Scappoose Industrial Airpark''' {{airport codes||KSPB|SPB{{nobold|, formerly }}1S4}} is a public use [[airport]] located one nautical mile (1.85&nbsp;km) northeast of the [[central business district]] of [[Scappoose, Oregon|Scappoose]], in [[Columbia County, Oregon|Columbia County]], [[Oregon]], [[United States]].<ref name=\"FAA\" /> It is owned and operated by the Port of Columbia County, an Oregon [[port district]] and [[municipal corporation]], on behalf of district residents. According to the FAA's [[National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems]] for 2009\u20132013, it is categorized as a ''[[general aviation]]'' airport.<ref>[http://www.faa.gov/airports/planning_capacity/npias/ National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems] for 2009\u20132013: [http://www.faa.gov/airports/planning_capacity/npias/reports/media/2009/npias_2009_appA_part4.pdf Appendix A: Part 4 (PDF, 1.61 MB)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606180725/http://www.faa.gov/airports/planning_capacity/npias/reports/media/2009/npias_2009_appA_part4.pdf |date=2011-06-06 }}. Federal Aviation Administration. Updated 15 October 2008.</ref>\n\nAlthough many U.S. airports use the same three-letter [[location identifier]] for the [[Federal Aviation Administration|FAA]] and [[International Air Transport Association|IATA]], this airport is assigned '''SPB''' by the FAA but has no designation from the IATA<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.gcmap.com/airport/KSPB | title = Scappoose Industrial Airpark (ICAO: KSPB, FAA: SPB) | publisher = Great Circle Mapper | accessdate = 29 May 2010}}</ref> (which assigned '''SPB''' to\n[[Charlotte Amalie Harbor Seaplane Base]] in [[Charlotte Amalie, United States Virgin Islands|Charlotte Amalie]], [[Saint Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.gcmap.com/airport/SPB | title = Charlotte Amalie Harbor SPB (IATA: SPB, FAA: VI22) | publisher = Great Circle Mapper | accessdate = 29 May 2010}}</ref>).\n\nSeveral privately held firms in the general aviation manufacturing industry are headquartered at the Scappoose Industrial Airpark.\n\n== Facilities and aircraft ==\nScappoose Industrial Airpark covers an area of {{convert|196|acre|ha|lk=on}} at an [[elevation]] of 58 feet (18 m) above [[mean sea level]]. It has one [[runway]] designated 15/33 with an [[asphalt]] surface measuring 5,100 by 100 feet (1,554 x 30 m).<ref name=\"FAA\" />\n\nFor the 12-month period ending April 29, 2009, the airport had 75,500 aircraft operations, an average of 206 per day: 93% [[general aviation]], 7% [[air taxi]], and <1% [[military aviation|military]]. At that time there were 57 aircraft based at this airport: 75% single-[[aircraft engine|engine]], 2% multi-engine, 2% [[helicopter]] and 21% [[ultralight]].<ref name=\"FAA\" />\n\nThe use of [[Ultralight]] type [[Paramotor]] is not currently accepted by airport management despite federal funding. When asked for a response management hasn't responded or avoided inquiry's. Entry fee suggested but management is non-committal or non-responsive.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.portofcolumbiacounty.org/business-and-development/page/scappoose-industrial-airpark/ Scappoose Industrial Airpark]\n* [https://www.portofcolumbiacounty.org/ Port of Columbia County]\n* [http://msrmaps.com/map.aspx?t=1&s=11&lat=45.771&lon=-122.8635&w=500&h=1000&lp=---+None+--- Aerial image as of 5 August 2000] from [[USGS]] ''[[The National Map]]''\n* {{FAA-procedures|SPB}}\n{{US-airport-ga|SPB|-}}\n{{Airports in Oregon}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in Columbia County, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Scappoose, Oregon]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Airport\n| name         = Scappoose Industrial Airpark\n| image        = Scappoose Industrial Airpark Oregon.jpg\n| caption      = Hangars, planes, and runway\n| IATA         = <!--not SPB-->\n| ICAO         = KSPB\n| FAA          = SPB\n| type         = Public\n| owner-oper   = Port of Columbia County\n| city-served  = [[Scappoose, Oregon]]\n| location     = <!--if different than above-->\n| elevation-f  = 58\n| elevation-m  = 18\n| coordinates  = {{coord|45|46|16|N|122|51|43|W|region:US-OR_type:airport_scale:10000}}\n| website      = [https://www.portofcolumbiacounty.org/business-and-development/page/scappoose-industrial-airpark/ Port of Columbia County]\n| r1-number    = 15/33\n| r1-length-f  = 5,100\n| r1-length-m  = 1,554\n| r1-surface   = [[Asphalt]]\n| stat-year    = 2009\n| stat1-header = Aircraft operations\n| stat1-data   = 75,500\n| stat2-header = Based aircraft\n| stat2-data   = 57\n| footnotes    = Source: [[Federal Aviation Administration]]<ref name=\"FAA\">{{FAA-airport|ID=SPB|use=PU|own=PU|site=19598.*A}}. Federal Aviation Administration. Effective 8 April 2010.</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Scappoose Industrial Airpark''' {{airport codes||KSPB|SPB{{nobold|, formerly }}1S4}} is a public use [[airport]] located one nautical mile (1.85&nbsp;km) northeast of the [[central business district]] of [[Scappoose, Oregon|Scappoose]], in [[Columbia County, Oregon|Columbia County]], [[Oregon]], [[United States]].<ref name=\"FAA\" /> It is owned and operated by the Port of Columbia County, an Oregon [[port district]] and [[municipal corporation]], on behalf of district residents. According to the FAA's [[National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems]] for 2009\u20132013, it is categorized as a ''[[general aviation]]'' airport.<ref>[http://www.faa.gov/airports/planning_capacity/npias/ National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems] for 2009\u20132013: [http://www.faa.gov/airports/planning_capacity/npias/reports/media/2009/npias_2009_appA_part4.pdf Appendix A: Part 4 (PDF, 1.61 MB)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606180725/http://www.faa.gov/airports/planning_capacity/npias/reports/media/2009/npias_2009_appA_part4.pdf |date=2011-06-06 }}. Federal Aviation Administration. Updated 15 October 2008.</ref>\n\nAlthough many U.S. airports use the same three-letter [[location identifier]] for the [[Federal Aviation Administration|FAA]] and [[International Air Transport Association|IATA]], this airport is assigned '''SPB''' by the FAA but has no designation from the IATA<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.gcmap.com/airport/KSPB | title = Scappoose Industrial Airpark (ICAO: KSPB, FAA: SPB) | publisher = Great Circle Mapper | accessdate = 29 May 2010}}</ref> (which assigned '''SPB''' to\n[[Charlotte Amalie Harbor Seaplane Base]] in [[Charlotte Amalie, United States Virgin Islands|Charlotte Amalie]], [[Saint Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.gcmap.com/airport/SPB | title = Charlotte Amalie Harbor SPB (IATA: SPB, FAA: VI22) | publisher = Great Circle Mapper | accessdate = 29 May 2010}}</ref>).\n\nSeveral privately held firms in the general aviation manufacturing industry are headquartered at the Scappoose Industrial Airpark.\n\n== Facilities and aircraft ==\nScappoose Industrial Airpark covers an area of {{convert|196|acre|ha|lk=on}} at an [[elevation]] of 58 feet (18 m) above [[mean sea level]]. It has one [[runway]] designated 15/33 with an [[asphalt]] surface measuring 5,100 by 100 feet (1,554 x 30 m).<ref name=\"FAA\" />\n\nFor the 12-month period ending April 29, 2009, the airport had 75,500 aircraft operations, an average of 206 per day: 93% [[general aviation]], 7% [[air taxi]], and <1% [[military aviation|military]]. At that time there were 57 aircraft based at this airport: 75% single-[[aircraft engine|engine]], 2% multi-engine, 2% [[helicopter]] and 21% [[ultralight]].<ref name=\"FAA\" />\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.portofcolumbiacounty.org/business-and-development/page/scappoose-industrial-airpark/ Scappoose Industrial Airpark]\n* [https://www.portofcolumbiacounty.org/ Port of Columbia County]\n* [http://msrmaps.com/map.aspx?t=1&s=11&lat=45.771&lon=-122.8635&w=500&h=1000&lp=---+None+--- Aerial image as of 5 August 2000] from [[USGS]] ''[[The National Map]]''\n* {{FAA-procedures|SPB}}\n{{US-airport-ga|SPB|-}}\n{{Airports in Oregon}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in Columbia County, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Scappoose, Oregon]]\n", "name_user": "Starsbeam", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:Update Ultralight and Paramotor acceptance", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scappoose_Industrial_Airpark"}
{"title_page": "Jackie Cruz (soccer)", "text_new": "{{about|the Puerto Rican footballer|the Dominican American entertainer|Jackie Cruz}}\n{{short description|Association footballer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2015}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Jackie Cruz\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Jacqueline Marie Cruz Capuzelo\n| birth_name     = Jacqueline Marie Cruz<ref name=CBI>{{Cite web|url=https://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/jacqueline_marie_cruz_born_1986_17294968|title=Jacqueline Marie Cruz, Born 12/02/1986 in California|website=CaliforniaBirthIndex.org|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1986|12|2|df=y}}<ref name=CBI/>\n| birth_place    = [[San Mateo, California|San Mateo]], [[California]], United States\n| height         = 1.65 m<ref>{{Soccerway|177327|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = \n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1    = 2004\u20132006\n| youthclubs1    = [[San Jose State Spartans]]\n| youthyears2    = 2007\n| youthclubs2    = [[Cal State East Bay Pioneers]]\n| years1         = 2007\u20132009\n| years4         = 2010\n| years5         = 2011\u20132013\n| years6         = 2013\u20132015\n| years7         = 2015\u2013\n| clubs1         = [[San Francisco Nighthawks]]\n| clubs4         = [[California Storm]]\n| clubs5         = [[BV Cloppenburg (women)|BV Cloppenburg]]\n| clubs6         = [[Magdeburger FFC]]\n| clubs7         = [[FF USV Jena]]\n| caps1          = 5\n| caps2          = \n| caps3 = \n| caps4 = 23\n| caps5 = 33\n| caps6 = \n| caps7 = 9\n| goals1         = 0\n| goals2         = \n| goals3 = \n| goals4 = 1\n| goals5 = 5\n| goals6 = 7\n| goals7 = 0\n| nationalyears1 =  2008\u20132010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Puerto Rico women's national football team|Puerto Rico]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 14\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| pcupdate  = August 27, 2016\n}}\n{{Spanish name|Cruz|Capuzelo}}\n'''Jacqueline \u201cJackie\u201d Marie Cruz Capuzelo''' (born 2 December 1986) is an American-born Puerto Rican [[Women's association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]]. She has been a member of the [[Puerto Rico women's national football team|Puerto Rico women's national team]].<ref>[http://www.meta.pr/content/quinto-lugar-para-puerto-rico-en-el-futbol Fifth place for Puerto Rico in football] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903010820/http://www.meta.pr/content/quinto-lugar-para-puerto-rico-en-el-futbol |date=September 3, 2012 }} Meta: Mayag\u00fcez 2010</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nCruz previously played for [[Women's Premier Soccer League|WPSL]] sides [[San Francisco Nighthawks]],<ref>[http://www.sfnighthawks.com/newsp.php?news_id=31 Jackie Cruz named all-independent defensive playerof the year.] Nighthawks' website</ref> [[California Storm]]<ref>[http://www.sjsuspartans.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5600&ATCLID=205088845 SJSU soccer standout Jackie Cruz signs with European club] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407043831/http://www.sjsuspartans.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5600&ATCLID=205088845 |date=April 7, 2012 }}. [[San Jose State Spartans]]'s website</ref> and [[USV Jena (women)|USV Jena]] in [[Germany]]'s [[Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga (women)|Bundesliga]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100221224729/http://www.bvcdamen.de.vu/ 2011\u201312 squad] in Cloppenburg's website</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cruz, Jackie}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rico women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican expatriate women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate women's footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:American women's soccer players]]\n[[Category:Soccer players from C