{"title_page": "Canadian Wine Annual", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{more citations needed|date=November 2015}}\nThe '''''Canadian Wine Annual''''' was the yearly guide to Canadian [[winery|wineries]] from ''Wine Access'' magazine - a magazine about [[wine]] and food.<ref name=johns>{{cite web|title=Wine Access magazine is shut down|url=http://johnschreiner.blogspot.ca/2013/02/wine-access-magazine-is-shut-down.html|publisher=John Schreiner|accessdate=13 November 2015|date=9 February 2013}}</ref> The magazine was founded in 2006.<ref name=johns/> The ''Annual'' was published every spring and included a complete listing of Canadian wineries, as well as maps, accommodations and other travel information. Articles in the ''Annual'' examined, among other things, the Canadian wine industry and the [[enotourism]] industry.\n\nThe 2007 ''Annual'' included information on more than 300 wineries, divided into 5 regions: [[Ontario]]; [[British Columbia]]; [[Quebec]]; Atlantic; and the Prairies.\n\nResults from the Canadian Wine Awards (this competition, a property of ''Wine Access'', is held annually in late summer and results are originally printed in the December/January issue of the magazine) are printed in the ''Annual'', including the Performance Report of the Top 20 Canadian Wineries of the year.\n\nRegular contributors to the ''Canadian Wine Annual'' included: John Schreiner; Tony Aspler; Veronique Rivest; David Lawrason; Stuart Tobe; Jefferson Davis; Sean Wood; Kasey Wilson; Margaret Swaine; Mark Davidson; and Craig Pinhey.\n\nThe ''Annual'' ceased publication with the February / March 2013 issue.<ref>{{cite news|title=Farewell Wine Access|url=https://winecountrybc.wordpress.com/2013/02/08/farewell-wine-access/|accessdate=13 November 2015|work=Wine Country|date=8 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070928143046/http://www.wineaccess.ca/ ''Wine Access'']\n\n[[Category:2006 establishments in Canada]]\n[[Category:2013 disestablishments in Canada]]\n[[Category:Canadian annual magazines]]\n[[Category:Canadian lifestyle magazines]]\n[[Category:Defunct magazines of Canada]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 2006]]\n[[Category:Magazines disestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Wine magazines]]\n\n\n{{wine-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{ref improve|date=November 2015}}\nThe '''''Canadian Wine Annual''''' was the yearly guide to Canadian [[winery|wineries]] from ''Wine Access'' magazine - a magazine about [[wine]] and food.<ref name=johns>{{cite web|title=Wine Access magazine is shut down|url=http://johnschreiner.blogspot.ca/2013/02/wine-access-magazine-is-shut-down.html|publisher=John Schreiner|accessdate=13 November 2015|date=9 February 2013}}</ref> The magazine was founded in 2006.<ref name=johns/> The ''Annual'' was published every spring and included a complete listing of Canadian wineries, as well as maps, accommodations and other travel information. Articles in the ''Annual'' examined, among other things, the Canadian wine industry and the [[enotourism]] industry.\n\nThe 2007 ''Annual'' included information on more than 300 wineries, divided into 5 regions: [[Ontario]]; [[British Columbia]]; [[Quebec]]; Atlantic; and the Prairies.\n\nResults from the Canadian Wine Awards (this competition, a property of ''Wine Access'', is held annually in late summer and results are originally printed in the December/January issue of the magazine) are printed in the ''Annual'', including the Performance Report of the Top 20 Canadian Wineries of the year.\n\nRegular contributors to the ''Canadian Wine Annual'' included: John Schreiner; Tony Aspler; Veronique Rivest; David Lawrason; Stuart Tobe; Jefferson Davis; Sean Wood; Kasey Wilson; Margaret Swaine; Mark Davidson; and Craig Pinhey.\n\nThe ''Annual'' ceased publication with the February / March 2013 issue.<ref>{{cite news|title=Farewell Wine Access|url=https://winecountrybc.wordpress.com/2013/02/08/farewell-wine-access/|accessdate=13 November 2015|work=Wine Country|date=8 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n[https://web.archive.org/web/20070928143046/http://www.wineaccess.ca/ ''Wine Access'']\n\n[[Category:2006 establishments in Canada]]\n[[Category:2013 disestablishments in Canada]]\n[[Category:Annual magazines]]\n[[Category:Canadian lifestyle magazines]]\n[[Category:Defunct magazines of Canada]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 2006]]\n[[Category:Magazines disestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Wine magazines]]\n\n{{wine-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hmains", "label": "safe", "comment": "category refine, sort sequence", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canadian_Wine_Annual"}
