 Sports Archive\n| accessdate     = 10 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Spanish name|Reyes|Delgado}}\n'''Deysla Marie Reyes Delgado''' (born 23 January 1993) is a Puerto Rican [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for the [[Puerto Rico women's national football team|Puerto Rico women's national team]].\n\n==Early life==\nReyes was raised in [[Santurce, San Juan, Puerto Rico|Santurce]], [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.njcaa.org/sports/wsoc/2011-12/div1/teams/LaramieCountyCommunityCollege/roster.html|title=Laramie County Community College - Roster - NJCAA Stats|website=NJCAA|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.njcaa.org/sports/wsoc/2011-12/div1/teams/LaramieCountyCommunityCollege/players/DeyslaReyesDelgado.html|title=2011-12 - NJCAA Stats|website=NJCAA|accessdate=10 April 2020}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.golccc.com/sports/wsoc/2012-13/players/deyslareyesdelgadojb6v|website=Laramie County CC|title=Deysla Reyes Delgado {{!}}#4 {{!}}D {{!}}Laramie County Community College|accessdate=10 April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reyes, Deysla}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from San Juan, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:People from Santurce, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rico women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2010 Central American and Caribbean Games]]\n[[Category:College women's soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Valdosta State University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deysla_Reyes"}
